title: "Yilderim" by Lieutenant Colonel Hussein Husni Amir, T
description: "Yilderim" by Lieutenant Colonel Hussein Husni Amir, Turkish General Staff. "Yilderim" is the noise produced by electricity generated in clouds during a storm, example, he who attacks with the violence and rapidity of "Yilderim", ie in English like a bolt out of the blue. This was a Turkish Corps formed to defend Palestine from the invasion by the British forces under General Allenby from 1917 to the end of the war in 1918. Husni wrote the Turkish account of these events
